<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,1427,1453]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leme &amp; L. Kollmann" authorityYear="2011" box="[402,679,1428,1453]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurvipetala">
<emphasis box="[402,679,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Aechmea recurvipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found during a 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1109,1428,1454]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
survey conducted in Alto Cariri State Park with the support of the Instituto Estadual de Florestas (IEF) of 
<collectingRegion box="[1094,1255,1466,1492]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
. It is a member of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,290,1505,1530]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,290,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Aechmea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gaudich. ex Beer) Baker" authorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityName="Beer" box="[416,860,1505,1531]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Chevaliera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[416,546,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Chevaliera</emphasis>
(Gaudich. ex Beer) Baker
</taxonomicName>
, and belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1226,1505,1530]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis box="[1096,1226,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">A. conifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex. The closest relative is 
<taxonomicName authority="Leme (2010: 131)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="131" authorityYear="2010" box="[411,812,1544,1570]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterosepala">
<emphasis box="[411,593,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">A. heterosepala</emphasis>
Leme (2010: 131)
</taxonomicName>
, from which the new species differs by its erect floral bracts (vs. suberect), which are distinctly imbricate (vs. not imbricate toward the apex), not forming any pouches around the flowers (vs. forming a distinct utricle around the flowers); shorter sepals (
<quantity box="[1265,1394,1621,1647]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="22.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="22.0">22–23 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[151,278,1660,1686]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="29.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="29.0">29–30 mm</quantity>
long) with a mucronate apex (vs. apex long subulate-cuspidate), and by the narrowly ovate petals (vs. narrowly spatulate), which are shorter (
<quantity box="[695,828,1698,1724]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="22.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="21.0">21–23 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[882,1016,1698,1724]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="33.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="32.0">32–35 mm</quantity>
) and strongly spirally recurved at anthesis (vs. erect).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Since the identification of the species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[732,863,1776,1801]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis box="[732,863,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">A. conifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex can be a difficult task due to a similar general appearance of the species, an idenfitication key is presented below.
</paragraph>
